-- Abu Dhabi's Aabar Plans to Sell 3.3% Stake in Atlantia for $447 Million
-- B y   C a m i l l a   H a l l
-- 2010-11-02T05:14:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/abu-dhabi-s-aabar-plans-to-sell-3-3-stake-in-atlantia-for-447-million.html
Aabar Investments PJSC, the Abu Dhabi
government-controlled company that is the biggest shareholder in
luxury carmaker Daimler AG, plans to sell its 3.3 percent stake
in Italy’s Atlantia SpA for 321 million euros ($447 million).  “Aabar entered into sale and purchase agreements for the
sale of its entire 3.3 percent stake in Atlantia for an
aggregate purchase price of 321 million euros,” according to a
preliminary bond prospectus by Aabar’s owner International
Petroleum Investments Co. “Completion of the sales is expected
shortly subject to closing conditions.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camilla Hall in Dubai at 
